: the serialization test should pass, while the deserialization test might only catch MissingReflection errors, which isn't allowed. If there's no deserialization, then there's no readObject to worry about. I wonder if using `ObjectInputFilter` could help, but I'm doubting it. I thought about using `sun.reflect.ReflectionFactory` for construction, but that doesn't seem viable. Reading through the BCElGamalPrivateKey source, I see package-private constructors aren't accessible.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_7c6u4hpqzp5ftZfDFsmIaiyC|fc_0cc855b30ab4c6fe016a25d8a2f33c81968571c6c4f1d76cda", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport json\nj=json.load(open('tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json'))\nfor c in j['classes']:\n for cs in c['callSites']:\n  if cs['line'] is None and cs['covered']:\n   print('covered unknown', c['className'], cs['frame']); raise SystemExit\nprint('none')\nPY"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 812, "output": 1541, "cacheRead": 56832, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59185, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780865150923, "responseId": "resp_0cc855b30ab4c6fe016a25d87fa5d48196b44da7218c3309a4"}}
